snippet.textDisplay:
Its not a Shepherd's Pie but a Cottage Pie. It is a very authentic Cottage Pie though. Shepherd's and Cottage Pies were always made from left overs not ground/minced meat.
The difference between a Shepherd and a Cottage Pie? The meat. A shepherd would make a pie from the animals he tended to, Sheep. If the pie has mutton, hoggart or lamb in it then its a Shepherd's Pie. Any other meat and its a Cottage Pie.
